<h1>Automatic Marker for Vector Graphics Drawing Tasks</h1>

<div class="row">
  
  <div class="col-sm-6">
    <h3>Instructions</h3>
    <p>
      In each step, you will be presented with a downloadable graphic.
      Recreate/trace it in a vector graphics editor of your choice (Adobe
      Illustrator, CorelDRAW, or Inkscape).
    </p>
    <p>
      Once who have completed a task, save/export it as an SVG using the
      export guidelines listed in the column to the right
      <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span>
    </p>
    <p>
      There are six graphics in all, and a brief questionnaire to complete at
      the end.
    </p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="col-sm-6 alert-info editors">
    <h4>Adobe Illustrator</h4>
    <p>
      Upon export, the CSS Properties field (under Advanced Options) must be
      set to <strong>Style Attributes</strong> (or Inline Style).
    </p>
    <h4>CorelDRAW</h4>
    <p>
      Upon export, the Styling Options field (under General Options) must be
      set to <strong>Inline Stylesheet</strong>.
    </p>
    <h4>Inkscape</h4>
    <p>
      Inkscape does not provide styling options in the export dialogue.
      Simply save the graphic as a <strong>plain SVG</strong>.
    </p>
  </div>
  
</div>

<h2>Enter your details and begin:</h2>

<div class="row">
  
  <div class="col-sm-6">
    Firstname:
    <br />
    {{input type="text" value=firstname class="form-control col-sm-6" autofocus="autofocus"}}
  </div>
  
  <div class="col-sm-6">
    Surname:
    <br />
    {{input type="text" value=surname class="form-control col-sm-6"}}
  </div>
  
</div>

<hr />

<input type="submit" value="Begin" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg btn-block" {{action 'begin'}} disabled={{isDisabled}} />
